inside of my sister's guinea pig,Snowball,
我基本看到我姐的豚鼠-雪球球的内部咯

75
00:04:48,570 --> 00:04:51,050
before he caught fire.
然后它就着火了

76
00:04:51,690 --> 00:04:53,610
It led to an interesting
expression in our house:
于是就有了我家那句玩笑话

77
00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:57,250
Not a Snowball's
chance in a CAT scanner.
雪球别想在扫描仪里活命
(CAT=猫 雪球=豚鼠)

78
00:04:58,450 --> 00:05:01,040
Uh,Sheldon?
嗯 Sheldon?

79
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:03,220
Excuse me.
抱歉离开下

80
00:05:03,230 --> 00:05:06,560
When I come back,just for fun,the
subject will be alternative history.
等我回来 为了有趣些
话题将是:历史的分叉点

81
00:05:06,570 --> 00:05:09,400
Specifically,how would the
Civil War have gone differently
尤其是 如果林肯是未来送来的机器人

82
00:05:09,430 --> 00:05:13,270
if Lincoln had been a
robot sent from the future?
内战会有如何不同的发展呢?

83
00:05:17,410 --> 00:05:20,930
Look at that,there's
even pasta left over.
看嘛 还有没吃完的意面

84
00:05:20,940 --> 00:05:23,770
Do you understand that this
was supposed to be a date?
你知道这本应是次约会吗?

85
00:05:23,780 --> 00:05:25,430
I do. Do you?
我知道哦 你知道吗?

86
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:29,850
Because frankly,you've been in
a foul mood since I sat down.
老实讲 因为自我坐下
你的心情就一直很恶劣

87
00:05:32,150 --> 00:05:34,300
Okay,here's my question.
好嘛 那我问你

88
00:05:34,310 --> 00:05:37,200
Why did you sit down?
你为啥要坐下来?

89
00:05:37,210 --> 00:05:38,140
To help.
帮忙呀

90
00:05:38,150 --> 00:05:42,910
Look,if you fail at this relationship,and
history suggests you will,
如果你这次搞砸 历史证明你会哟

91
00:05:43,860 --> 00:05:48,670
then we risk losing the medical officer
that our landing party has always needed.
那我们有可能失去登陆先头部队
一直需要的医疗官哦

92
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:54,280
What landing party?
什么登陆先头部队?
(星际旅行每次都会先遣队登陆探险)

93
00:05:54,310 --> 00:05:59,720
You're Kirk,I'm Spock,Wolowitz is Scotty,Koothrappali
is the guy who always gets killed...
你是Kirk 我是Spock Wolowitz是Scotty
Koothrappali是那个老被干掉的角色...

94
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:04,960
and now we've got McCoy.
现在我们可算找到McCoy了
(McCoy星际中的医疗官)

95
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:15,790
So,we're all standing around looking
at the post-op X ray and there it is,
我们都围着看手术后的x光片

96
00:06:15,810 --> 00:06:18,510
clear as day,right in
the guy's chest cavity...
十分显眼 就在那家伙的胸腔里

97
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:21,430
one of my earrings.
我的一只耳环

98
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:24,570
Oh,my God,what did you do?
我的天 你都做了些什么啊?

99
00:06:24,580 --> 00:06:25,890
What do you think I did?
我还能做什么?

100
00:06:25,910 --> 00:06:31,290
I discreetly slipped off the other earring,put it
in my pocket and then got the hell out of there!
我小心地取下另外一只
放进口袋 然后溜了出来!

101
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:35,330
I have a bone to pick with you,sir.
先生 我可得和你评评理

102
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,870
- Hi,Sheldon.
- Hi,Stephanie.
- 你好 Sheldon
- 你好 Stephanie

103
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:42,500
I'm sorry I'm late,but your companion
left the most indecipherable invitation.
抱歉 迟来了 你的同伴留下了
最难破译的邀请函

104
00:06:42,910 --> 00:06:45,950
What invitation?
什么邀请?

105
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:48,050
We're going to the movies.
我们看电影去了

106
00:06:48,070 --> 00:06:51,610
What movie? What theater? What time?
啥电影 啥影院 啥时候

107
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:56,480
If you were trying to make it impossible to
locate you,you couldn't have done a better job.
如果你想让别人找不到你
你应该做的更绝一点

108
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:59,590
Oh,clearly I could have.
哦 很明显我是该这么做

109
00:07:00,260 --> 00:07:03,170
It took me nearly 20 minutes to go through
the browser history on your computer to see
我用了将近20分钟
查看你电脑里的历史记录

110
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:06,060
what movie times you looked up.
查找你都搜索过什么电影

111
